@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

   @{b}Introduction@{ub}
  --------------

   AvailCPU visualizes the CPU usage.

   I wrote this simple program to seek when a program  is  consuming  much
   CPU power or just gone to heaven.

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

   @{b}System requirements@{ub}
  ---------------------

   AvailCPU (should work) works on all Amigas with OS 2.0 or higher.
@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Features"

   @{b}Features@{ub}
  ----------

  ¯ 100% Assembler

@endnode
@node "Distribution" "Distribution"

   @{b}Distribution@{ub}
  --------------

   This program should be published on every public medium, as long as all
   files  in  the archive are unchanged. If this medium is a CD I expect a
   free copy. (AminetCDs excluded)

   @{b}AvailCPU is Mailware.@{ub}

   I expect from everybody, who uses AvailCPU regularly,  to  send  me  an
   email  or postcard. I think this does not hurt anybody, and I will have
   more fun to integrate new features.

   @{b}I am not liable for injures or data loss caused by AvailCPU! The use of
   AvailCPU is on your own responsibility !!!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "HowToInstall" "How to install AvailCPU"

   @{b}How to install AvailCPU@{ub}
  ---------------------------

   Just copy AvailCPU into your C: drawer!

   If you want to start AvailCPU automaticaly, then insert  the  following
   line into your s:user-startup:

   run <>NIL: AvailCPU

   Thats all!

@endnode
